doc.previous: The Puget Sound region is a coastal area of the Pacific Northwest in the U S state of Washington including Puget Sound the Puget Sound lowlands and the surrounding region roughly west of the Cascade Range and east of the Olympic Mountains It is characterised by a complex array of saltwater bays islands and peninsulas carved out by prehistoric glaciers
